<title>USA: Rubin optimistic on chances of US financial reform.</title>
<headline>Rubin optimistic on chances of US financial reform.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-06-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>U.S. Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin said Tuesday he believed financial services reform could be achieved in the current congress.</p>
<p>&quot;In terms of the political situation, I think we can get this done,&quot; Rubin told reporters after testifying to the House Banking Committee on the issue.</p>
<p>&quot;I think there is a powerful public interest that lies in financial modernization legislation,&quot; he said.</p>
